doc.value:
This flow looks for files matching given criteria and acts on them.

  FileFinder searches for files that match glob expressions.  The "action"
  (e.g. Download) is applied to files that match all given "conditions".
  Matches are then written to the results collection. If there are no
  "conditions" specified, "action" is just applied to all found files.

  FileFinder replaces these deprecated flows: FetchFiles, FingerprintFile
  and SearchFileContent.
  

  Call Spec:
    flow.GRRFlow.StartFlow(client_id=client_id, flow_name="FileFinder", paths=paths, pathtype=pathtype, conditions=conditions, action=action, process_non_regular_files=process_non_regular_files, follow_links=follow_links, xdev=xdev, upload_token=upload_token)

  Args:
    action
      description: 
      type: FileFinderAction
      default: None

    conditions
      description: These conditions will be applied to all files that match the path arguments.
      type: 
      default: None

    follow_links
      description: Should symbolic links be followed in recursive directory listings.
      type: RDFBool
      default: 0

    paths
      description: A path to glob that can contain %% expansions.
      type: 
      default: None

    pathtype
      description: Path type to glob in.
      type: EnumNamedValue
      default: OS

    process_non_regular_files
      description: Look both into regular files and non-regular files (devices, named pipes, sockets). NOTE: This is very dangerous and should be used with care.
      type: RDFBool
      default: 0

    upload_token
      description: An upload token to use with the direct upload functionality. This token contains the hmac authenticated policy that determines for how long the client is allowed to upload files to the server. This is comparable to the policy document used by GCS: https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/xml-api/post-object#policydocument 
      type: UploadToken
      default: None

    xdev
      description: Behavior when ecountering device boundaries while doing recursive searches.
      type: EnumNamedValue
      default: LOCAL

List running processes on a system.

  Call Spec:
    flow.GRRFlow.StartFlow(client_id=client_id, flow_name="ListProcesses", filename_regex=filename_regex, fetch_binaries=fetch_binaries, connection_states=connection_states)

  Args:
    connection_states
      description: Network connection states to match. If a process has any network connections in any status listed here, it will be considered a match
      type: 
      default: None

    fetch_binaries
      description: 
      type: RDFBool
      default: 0

    filename_regex
      description: Regex used to filter the list of processes.
      type: RegularExpression
      default: .

Run a report and send the result via email.

  Call Spec:
    flow.GRRFlow.StartFlow(client_id=client_id, flow_name="RunReport", report_name=report_name, email=email)

  Args:
    email
      description: The email address that messages will be sent to.
      type: DomainEmailAddress
      default: None

    report_name
      description: The name of the report to run.
      type: ReportName
      default: None
